{"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/HashFunc"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"HashFunc"},{"text":" = ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GHashFunc","text":"GHashFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The function is passed a key and should return a ","type":"text"},{"code":"guint","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" hash value."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The functions ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_direct_hash()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_int_hash()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"g_str_hash()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"hash functions which can be used when the key is a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gpointer"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"gint","type":"codeVoice"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gchar"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" respectively."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_direct_hash()"},{"text":" is also the appropriate hash function for keys","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the form ","type":"text"},{"code":"GINT_TO_POINTER (n)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (or similar macros).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A good hash functions should produce"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hash values that are evenly distributed over a fairly large range."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The modulus is taken with the hash table size (a prime number) to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"find the ‘bucket’ to place each key into. The function should also","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be very fast, since it is called for each key lookup."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that the hash functions provided by GLib have these qualities,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"but are not particularly robust against manufactured keys that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"cause hash collisions. Therefore, you should consider choosing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a more secure hash function when using a GHashTable with keys"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that originate in untrusted data (such as HTTP requests).","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_str_hash()"},{"text":" in that situation might make your application","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"vulnerable to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/lwn.net\/Articles\/474912\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The key to choosing a good hash is unpredictability.  Even"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cryptographic hashes are very easy to find collisions for when the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"remainder is taken modulo a somewhat predictable prime number.  There"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"must be an element of randomness that an attacker is unable to guess."}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/hashfunc"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifies the type of the hash function which is passed to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_hash_table_new()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/HashTable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is created."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"HashFunc"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Type Alias","role":"symbol","title":"HashFunc","externalID":"s:4GLib8HashFunca","symbolKind":"typealias","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"HashFunc","kind":"identifier"}]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/HashTable":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"HashTable","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/HashTable","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"HashTable"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/hashtable","title":"HashTable","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/HashTable"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data structure to represent a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"data-structures.html#hash-tables","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". It should only be accessed via the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"following functions."}]},"https://lwn.net/Articles/474912/":{"url":"https:\/\/lwn.net\/Articles\/474912\/","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/lwn.net\/Articles\/474912\/","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Algorithmic Complexity Attacks"}],"title":"Algorithmic Complexity Attacks"},"data-structures.html#hash-tables":{"url":"data-structures.html#hash-tables","type":"link","identifier":"data-structures.html#hash-tables","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hash Table"}],"title":"Hash Table"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/HashFunc":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/hashfunc","title":"HashFunc","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/HashFunc","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"HashFunc"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Specifies the type of the hash function which is passed to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_hash_table_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" when a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/HashTable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is created.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"HashFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"}}}